<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06092069 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06092069 </ACCESS><CAPTION>  Photo; PHOTO: Barkley  </CAPTION><DESCRIPT>  PROFESSIONAL; BASKETBALL; BRIEF  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Philadelphia forward Charles Barkley suffered a torn ligament in his left kneeSunday during the 76ers' 110-101 win over visiting Cleveland and will besidelined at least two weeks and possibly for the remainder of the season.;   Barkley, who missed seven games earlier this season because of a back injury,will undergo tests today.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Sports  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  INJURY MAY END SEASON FOR BARKLEYNO BAN FOR TARPLEY; ARREST DONE WITH CARE  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  NBA Notebook  </MEMO><TEXT>     He was hurt Sunday when he bumped into teammate Rick Mahorn midway throughthe third period.;    Barkley was suspended for one game last week and fined$10,000 by the NBA after he spit at fans during a game at New Jersey.;   During a taped interview Sunday on NBC, he said: &quot;Sometimes the things I doare obviously wrong.&quot;;  NO BAN FOR TARPLEY: Dallas Mavericks forward RoyTarpley apparently won't be banned from the league after his arrest onsuspicion of driving while intoxicated.;    Tarpley, who twice has violatedthe NBA's anti-drug policy and has been told to stay away from drugs andalcohol, was arrested Saturday in Dallas.;    A league spokesman said NBApolicy states that a player can't pick up a &quot;third strike&quot; unless he testspositive for cocaine or heroin.;    Police officers gingerly handled Tarpley'sarrest. A crowd of 80 bystanders included two onlookers who videotaped thescene. Others taunted Tarpley and police, said Sgt. Richard Baumgardner.;   After the arrest, Baumgardner said, Tarpley &quot;got into the front seat with me,and I didn't handcuff him because he said he didn't want that. I let him usemy (car phone) to call his attorney.&quot;  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  <